F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Ffarah-khan-reveals-nagarjuna-was-the-first-person-who-increased-her-fees-says-i-learned-discipline-from-south-film-industry%2Farticleshow%2F105297905.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20What%20Did%20The%20Biden-Xi%20Meet%20Really%20Achieve%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden-Xi%20meeting%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20APEC%20(Asia-Pacific%20Economic%20Cooperation)%20summit%20hasn't%2C%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20produced%20any%20path-breaking%20results.%20If%20the%20objective%20was%20to%20bring%20about%20stability%20in%20ties%2C%20it%20is%20doubtful%20if%20that%20has%20been%20achieved.%20The%20deep%20differences%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20on%20the%20political%2C%20economic%2C%20technological%2C%20and%20strategic%20fronts%20cannot%20be%20bridged%20so%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStability%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20through%20verbal%20positions.%20Policy%20changes%20are%20required.%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20foresee%20China%20changing%20its%20approach%20to%20sovereignty%20issues%2C%20be%20it%20Taiwan%2C%20the%20South%20China%20and%20East%20China%20Seas%2C%20or%20elsewhere.%20It%20is%20not%20going%20to%20curb%20its%20Belt%20and%20Road%20initiative%20that%20brings%20more%20and%20more%20countries%20into%20its%20economic%20and%20political%20fold.%20It%20will%20continue%20to%20expand%20its%20influence%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20globe%20to%20become%20a%20rival%20power%20to%20the%20US.%20It%20is%20not%20going%20to%20slow%20down%20its%20naval%20expansion.%20It%20is%20not%20going%20to%20slow%20down%20its%20naval%20expansion.%20It%20plans%20to%20expand%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%2C%20develop%20new%20capabilities%20to%20push%20back%20the%20US%20navy%20from%20its%20coast%20as%20far%20as%20possible%2C%20retain%20control%20over%20some%20critical%20raw%20materials%20and%20technologies%20to%20buttress%20its%20power%20ambitions%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20It%20is%20already%20eating%20into%20US%20influence%20in%20various%20critical%20geographies%2C%20as%2C%20for%20example%2C%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20which%20raises%20increasing%20geopolitical%20challenges%20to%20American%20power.%20China's%20declared%20ambitions%20with%20time%20lines%20to%20become%20central%20to%20global%20governance%20by%202049%20will%20not%20be%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20too%2C%20is%20not%20going%20to%20step%20back%20from%20its%20strategy%20at%20political%2C%20technology%20and%20military%20levels%20to%20curb%20China's%20threatening%20rise.%20Its%20policy%20of%20strengthening%20alliances%20in%20the%20western%20Pacific%20will%20continue.%20It%20will%20continue%20to%20arm%20Taiwan.%20The%20Indo-Pacific%20concept%2C%20the%20deepening%20of%20the%20Quad%2C%20or%20the%20Aukus%20alliance%20will%20continue%20to%20underpin%20its%20Asia%20policy%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20deterring%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20will%20continue%20to%20pursue%20a%20policy%20of%20denying%20China%20access%20to%20highly%20advanced%20technologies%20such%20as%20semi-conductors%2C%20building%20domestic%20capabilities%20to%20reduce%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Edependence%20on%20China%20in%20critical%20areas%2C%20prevent%20intellectual%20property%20theft%2C%20restrict%20Chinese%20investments%20in%20sensitive%20areas%20and%20push%20Europe%20in%20this%20direction%2C%20create%20trusted%20and%20resilient%20supply%20chains%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20dependence%20on%20China%2C%20do%20%26quot%3Bfriend-shoring%26quot%3B%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStability%20in%20US-China%20ties%20also%20depends%20on%20more%20stability%20in%20the%20global%20system.%20The%20ongoing%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20the%20US%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20that%20distort%20ties%20between%20third%20countries%20and%20Russia%20and%20impinge%20on%20the%20global%20financial%20system%2C%20the%20growing%20strategic%20closeness%20between%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20the%20fall-out%20of%20the%20dangerous%20conflict%20erupting%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20the%20ineffectiveness%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20create%20instabilities%20that%20also%20put%20strains%20on%20US-China%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20both%20sides%20some%20tactical%20adjustments%20can%2C%20however%2C%20be%20made%2C%20and%20this%20was%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20Biden-Xi%20meeting.%20The%20US%20has%20long%20sought%20to%20put%20some%20guardrails%20in%20place%20and%20prevent%20its%20differences%20with%20China%20on%20Taiwan%20and%20the%20South%20China%20and%20East%20China%20Seas%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Efrom%20escalating%20into%20an%20actual%20military%20conflict.%20Given%20the%20number%20of%20incidents%20of%20dangerously%20close%20contact%20between%20the%20naval%20ships%20and%20planes%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20in%20this%20region%2C%20the%20US%20has%20been%20pushing%20for%20the%20resumption%20of%20military%20contacts%20cancelled%20by%20China%20in%20August%202022.%20China%20had%20also%20suspended%20talks%20with%20the%20US%20on%20climate%20change.%20The%20US%20wanted%20to%20resume%20them%20as%20engaging%20China%20as%20the%20world's%20largest%20carbon%20dioxide%20emitter%20was%20essential%20to%20addressing%20climate%20change%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20read-out%20of%20the%20Biden-Xi%20meeting%20shows%20the%20limited%20results%20achieved.%20Even%20allowing%20that%20Biden%20had%20to%20appear%20tough%20in%20his%20exchange%20with%20Xi%20to%20ward%20off%20accusations%20by%20the%20Republicans%20that%20he%20is%20weak%20on%20China%2C%20and%20also%20appear%20responsive%20to%20the%20anti-China%20mood%20in%20the%20American%20public%2C%20the%20read-out%20does%20not%20suggest%20any%20re-set%20of%20bilateral%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20insisted%20that%20the%20US%20and%20China%20are%20in%20competition%20and%20that%20the%20US%20will%20invest%20in%20sources%20of%20strength%20at%20home%20and%20align%20with%20allies%20and%20partners%2C%20but%20that%20the%20US%20wants%20to%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Emanage%20competition%20responsibly%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20conflict%20and%20avoid%20confrontation.%20He%20reaffirmed%20support%20for%20a%20free%20and%20open%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20and%20the%20East%20China%20Sea%2C%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20and%20overflight%2C%20and%20underlined%20America's%20iron%20clad%20commitment%20to%20defending%20its%20allies.%20He%20warned%20against%20any%20unilateral%20change%20of%20status%20quo%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20called%20for%20Chinese%20restraint.%20He%20mentioned%20China's%20unfair%20trade%20practices%20and%20non-market%20economic%20practices.%20He%20was%20clear%20on%20preventing%20advanced%20US%20technologies%20from%20being%20used%20to%20undermine%20America's%20national%20security%2C%20though%20without%20unduly%20limiting%20trade%20and%20investment.%20He%20also%20spoke%20of%20America's%20international%20human%20rights%20commitments%20and%20specified%20concerns%20about%20human%20rights%20in%20Xinjiang%2C%20Tibet%20and%20Hong%20Kong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20more%20positive%20side%2C%20the%20US%20has%20been%20successful%20in%20restoring%20the%20high%20level%20military-to-military%20cooperation%20with%20China.%20The%20US-China%20Defence%20Policy%20Coordination%20talks%2C%20the%20Maritime%20Consultation%20Agreement%20meeting%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Etelephone%20communication%20between%20theatre%20commanders%20will%20be%20resumed.%20On%20the%20flow%20of%20Chinese%20produced%20Fentanyl%20through%20Mexico%20to%20the%20US%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20agreed%20to%20cooperate%20in%20addressing%20global%20illicit%20drug%20manufacturing.%20US%20and%20China%20will%20also%20address%20risks%20of%20advanced%20AI%20systems%20and%20improved%20AI%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Xi%20said%20at%20his%20meeting%20with%20Biden%20and%20to%20the%20US%20CEOs%20shows%20that%20while%20the%20Chinese%20President%20adopted%20a%20conciliatory%20tone%20and%20avoided%20getting%20into%20a%20robust%20spat%20with%20Biden%20-%20like%20in%20Alaska%20between%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20and%20China's%20Communist%20Party%20foreign%20affairs%20chief%20Yang%20Jiechi%20in%20March%202021%20-%20his%20pushback%20on%20some%20issues%20was%20politely%20firm.%20Taiwan%20was%20non-negotiable%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20affirmed%20that%20it%20will%20inevitably%20become%20part%20of%20China.%20He%20asked%20the%20US%20to%20stop%20arming%20Taiwan%20and%20support%20peaceful%20reunification.%20He%20also%20cautioned%20that%20military%20communication%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20would%20be%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20equality%20and%20mutual%20respect.%20He%20noted%20that%20US%20actions%20were%20stifling%20China's%20development%20and%20that%20the%20US%20should%20not%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Escheme%20to%20suppress%20or%20contain%20China.%20Both%20sides%20should%20understand%20each%20others%20'bottom%20lines.%20He%20asked%20the%20US%20not%20to%20interfere%20in%20China's%20internal%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fundamental%20question%20was%20whether%20the%20US%20and%20China%20were%20rivals%20or%20partners%2C%20Xi%20said.%20If%20the%20US%20considered%20China%20as%20its%20biggest%20rival%2C%20the%20most%20significant%20geopolitical%20challenge%20and%20an%20ever%20pressing%20threat%2C%20then%20wrong%20policies%2C%20wrong%20actions%20and%20wrong%20results%20will%20follow.%20Xi%20expressed%20China's%20willingness%20to%20be%20a%20partner%20and%20a%20friend%20to%20the%20US.%20There%20were%20the%20usual%20references%20to%20win-win%20cooperation%2C%20meeting%20each%20other%20half%20way%20and%20handling%20differences%20calmly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20press%20conference%2C%20in%20answer%20to%20a%20question%2C%20Biden%20called%20Xi%20a%20dictator%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20he%20was%20the%20leader%20of%20communist%20country%20with%20a%20system%20unlike%20that%20of%20the%20US%2C%20and%20this%20has%20been%20played%20up%20by%20the%20media%20as%20a%20major%20faux%20pas.%20This%20time%2C%20unlike%20on%20an%20earlier%20occasion%2C%20when%20Biden%20called%20Xi%20a%20dictator%2C%20the%20Chinese%20reaction%20has%20been%20more%20muted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20can%20switch%2C%20as%20the%20occasion%20demands%2C%20from%20wolf%20warrior%20diplomacy%20to%20a%20veneer%20of%20sweet%20reasonableness%20and%20project%20itself%20a%20country%20that%20is%20unfairly%20targeted%20whereas%20it%20is%20a%20positive%20global%20citizen.%20Nothing%20it%20says%20can%20be%20taken%20merely%20at%20face%20value.%20It%20is%20buying%20time%20to%20build%20itself%20against%20the%20US.%20Will%20the%20US%20system%20be%20coherent%20enough%20to%20give%20it%20the%20time%20it%20needs%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700236920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fngtoubdg_joe-biden-xi-jinping_625x300_16_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhat-did-the-biden-xi-meet-really-achieve-4583642%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Biden-Xi%20meeting%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20APEC%20(Asia-Pacific%20Economic%20Cooperation)%20summit%20hasn't%2C%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20produced%20any%20path-breaking%20results.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhat-did-the-biden-xi-meet-really-achieve-4583642%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhat-did-the-biden-xi-meet-really-achieve-4583642%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2