C%20it%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fhike-in-risk-weights-to-hit-banks-capital-adequacy-by-60-bps-s-p-ratings-123111700731_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fhike-in-risk-weights-to-hit-banks-capital-adequacy-by-60-bps-s-p-ratings-123111700731_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fhike-in-risk-weights-to-hit-banks-capital-adequacy-by-60-bps-s-p-ratings-123111700731_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Majestic%20Aerial%20Course%20of%20B.N.%20Goswamy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17171359%2FF_HahMAaIAARLj6.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELegendary%20art%20historian%20B.N.%20Goswamy%20passed%20away%20on%20November%2017%2C%202023.%20He%20was%2090.%20Goswamy%20was%20the%20recipient%20of%20the%20Padma%20Shri%20and%20the%20Padma%20Bhushan.%20The%20following%20was%20written%20by%20Laila%20Tyabji%20as%20a%20Facebook%20post%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20with%20minor%20edits%20and%20her%20permission.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20by%20one%2C%20the%20candles%20that%20illuminated%20one%E2%80%99s%20mind%20space%20are%20being%20blown%20out%20%E2%80%93%20Ela%20Ben%2C%20Brij%20Bhasin%2C%20Jasleen%20Dhamija%2C%20and%20now%20Professor%20B.N.%20Goswamy%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20heard%20Professor%20Goswamy%20before%20I%20actually%20met%20him%20%E2%80%93%20attending%20every%20talk%20he%20gave%20in%20Delhi%3B%20so%20enjoying%20the%20theatre%20of%20the%20man%20as%20well%20as%20his%20towering%20intellect.%20His%20wonderful%20rich%20deep%20voice%2C%20his%20command%20of%20and%20skilfully%20apposite%20use%20of%20Urdu%2C%20Farsi%2C%20Punjabi%2C%20and%20English%20verse%2C%20his%20imposing%20height%20and%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impeccably%20tailored%20suits%20(sometimes%20relieved%20by%20a%20colourful%20silk%20scarf%2C%20or%20in%20winter%20by%20a%20pashmina%20shawl%20tossed%20casually%20over%20a%20shoulder)%3B%20his%20ability%20to%20adroitly%20lead%20us%20through%20the%20minutiae%20of%20scholarship%20and%20research%20to%20an%20exciting%20revelation%20of%20a%20new%20insight%20or%20idea%20%E2%80%93%20making%20the%20journey%20as%20well%20as%20the%20arrival%20enthralling%2C%20his%20humour%20and%20his%20erudition%20both%20worn%20lightly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20first%20got%20to%20know%20each%20other%20as%20fellow%20members%20of%20the%20Crafts%20Museum%20Acquisitions%20Committee%20through%20the%201990s.%20Each%20meeting%20added%20so%20much%20to%20my%20understanding%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20of%20Indian%20art%2C%20but%20of%20worlds%20past%20and%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20was%20deeply%20touched%20when%20in%202011%20I%20reviewed%20his%20wonderful%20biography%20of%20Nain%20Sukh%20of%20Guler%2C%20the%20master%2018th%20century%20miniature%20painter%20from%20the%20Kangra%20valley%2C%20for%20the%20IIC%20Journal%2C%20and%20he%20wrote%20to%20say%20how%20much%20he%20had%20liked%20what%20I%20had%20written.%20It%20is%20still%20one%20of%20my%20favourite%20books%20of%20a%20Sherlock%20Holmes-turned-art-historian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20such%20beautiful%20manners%2C%20always%20making%20one%20feel%20the%20giver%20rather%20than%20recipient%20of%20any%20interchange.%20When%20we%20were%20both%20together%20on%20the%20Crafts%20Museum%20Committee%2C%20no%20one%20was%20better%20at%20breaking%20the%20news%20to%20a%20hopeful%20dealer%20that%20the%20object%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20sell%20was%20spurious.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fart-history-cats-bn-goswamy-indian-cat%5C%22%3EThere%20Is%20No%20Real%20Dislike%20for%20Cats%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Art%20History%20Says%20as%20Much%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CYou%3C%2Fem%3E%20value%20it%2C%20and%20that%20is%20as%20important%20as%20it%20actually%20being%20an%20antique.%20Take%20it%20back%20home%20and%20enjoy%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20I%20remember%20his%20saying%20to%20one%20disgruntled%20vendor!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnforgettable%20too%2C%20was%20him%20holding%20a%20%3Cem%3Ethaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20early%2019th%20century%20Dhakai%20muslin%20in%20his%20arms%20%E2%80%93%20translucent%20and%20incredibly%20fine%2C%20as%20light%20and%20buoyant%20as%20a%20cloud.%20His%20expression%20was%20that%20of%20someone%20cradling%20his%20first%20grandchild!%20He%20then%20recited%20Agha%20Shahid%20Ali%E2%80%99s%20evocative%20poem%20on%20%E2%80%98Dhaka%20Gauzes%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20I%E2%80%99d%20heard%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20recall%20the%20release%20in%202013%20of%20a%20commemorative%20volume%20in%20honour%20of%20Professor%20Goswamy%E2%80%99s%2080th%20birthday.%20Dr%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20much%20beleaguered%20at%20the%20time%2C%20launched%20it%20at%20his%20residence%20with%20his%20usual%20dignity%2C%20warmth%20and%20unexpected%20humour.%20He%20and%20Professor%20Goswamy%20were%20classmates%2C%20and%20later%20colleagues%2C%20in%20college.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20Professor%20Goswamy%2C%20then%2080%2C%20was%20his%20usual%20charming%2C%20insightful%2C%20multi-lingually%20articulate%2C%20impeccably%20dressed%20self%20(he%20was%20one%20scholar%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20dressed%20in%20a%20Fabindia%20kurta!)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20negative%20was%20the%20security%20rigmarole%20of%20getting%20into%20the%20PM%E2%80%99s%20house%2C%20including%20a%20transfer%20from%20ones%20own%20car%20into%20an%20official%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20him%20too%20at%20one%20of%20our%20Dastkar%20Bazaars%2C%20making%20me%20take%20him%20to%20all%20my%20most%20loved%20handloom%20weavers%2C%20so%20he%20could%20buy%20sarees%20for%20his%20beautiful%20wife%2C%20Karuna%2C%20a%20fellow%20scholar%20and%20historian%2C%20who%20had%20once%20been%20his%20student.%20When%20both%20our%20arms%20overflowed%20with%20silken%20fabrics%2C%20Karuna%20began%20protesting.%20She%20was%20firmly%20put%20into%20a%20chair%2C%20given%20a%20plate%20of%20chaat%20and%20jalebis%2C%20and%20told%20not%20to%20interrupt%20our%20vital%20research!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaruna%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20and%20that%20of%20his%20son%20Apu%2C%20greatly%20saddened%20his%20latter%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%20on%20Nain%20Sukh%2C%20Professor%20Goswamy%20writes%20of%20Nain%20Sukh%E2%80%99s%20magical%20artistry%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20a%20stray%20work%2C%20he%20simply%20picks%20an%20idea%2C%20refines%20it%2C%20gives%20it%20wings%2C%20and%20sends%20it%20soaring%20on%20its%20majestic%20aerial%20course.%E2%80%9D%20One%20could%20say%20the%20same%20of%20his%20own%20scholarship%2C%20writing%20and%20speaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20thoughts%20will%20soar%20on%2C%20even%20though%20he%20himself%20is%20gone.%20Nevertheless%2C%20we%20will%20sorely%20miss%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Flsil%2F%5C%22%3ELaila%20Tyabji%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20founder%20member%20and%20chairperson%20of%20Dastkar%2C%20an%20NGO%20working%20for%20the%20revival%20of%20traditional%20crafts%20in%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700221527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17171359%2FF_HahMAaIAARLj6.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fart-historian-bn-goswamy-obituary%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Among%20other%20things%2C%20no%20one%20was%20better%20at%20breaking%20the%20news%20to%20a%20hopeful%20dealer%20that%20the%20object%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20sell%20was%20spurious.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fart-historian-bn-goswamy-obituary%