n%25252520interaction%25252520with%25252520reporters%2Cterror%25252520attack%25252520on%25252520October%252525207.%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20is%20time%20for%20India%20to%20recognise%20Hamas%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20and%20hinted%20at%20the%20two%20sides%20having%20a%20dialogue%20along%20these%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-abandons-palestine-un-vote-switch-modi-taints-indian-army-comparing-surgical-strike-illegal-israeli-acts%5C%22%3Esimilar%20request%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202004%20by%20then%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20of%20Israel%2C%20Silvan%20Shalom%2C%20to%20designate%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20as%20terrorist%20outfits%20was%20rejected%20by%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Vajpayee%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministership%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20India%20actually%20condemned%20Israel%20for%20assassinating%20two%20Hamas%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20appalled%20by%20the%20killing%20in%20Gaza%20of%20Sheikh%20Ahmed%20Yassin%2C%20spiritual%20leader%20of%20Hamas%2C%20yesterday%20in%20an%20Israeli%20missile%20strike%2C%E2%80%9D%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fdelhi-appalled-the-day-after%2Fcid%2F760615%5C%22%3E%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20said%20in%20March%202004%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20later%2C%20when%20Israel%20killed%20his%20successor%2C%20Abdel%20Aziz%20Al-Rantisi%2C%20India%20again%20censured%20Tel%20Aviv.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20a%20special%20meeting%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.un.org%2Fen%2F2004%2Fsc8063.doc.htm%5C%22%3Ein%20April%202004%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ambassador%20Vijay%20Nambiar%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctargeted%20killing%20of%20al-Rantisi%20was%20unjustified%20and%20unacceptable%2C%20and%20could%20not%20be%20condoned%20under%20any%20circumstances.%C2%A0Such%20action%2C