ficant%20dive%20into%20the%20burgeoning%20scene%20of%20female%20rappers%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20offering%20a%20nuanced%20glimpse%20into%20their%20artistic%20endeavours.%20The%20emergence%20of%20female%20voices%20in%20Kashmiri%20rap%20marks%20a%20progressive%20step%20forward%2C%20challenging%20stereotypes%20and%20contributing%20to%20a%20more%20inclusive%20musical%20landscape.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FQ4eqqP11yN0%3Fsi%3DzBHHVEWHPKKxLaVI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700206154000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17125549%2FUntitled-design.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fwatch-the-resonance-of-resilience-kashmirs-musical-odyssey%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Each%20artist%20featured%20here%20brings%20their%20unique%20journey%20to%20the%20table%2C%20sharing%20their%20experiences%20with%20the%20rich%20cultural%20history%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20weaving%20their%20narratives%20in%20the%20poetic%20blend%20of%20Urdu%20and%20the%20Kashmiri%20language.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fwatch-the-resonance-of-resilience-kashmirs-musical-odyssey%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mind%20the%20Gap%3A%20A%20Slender%20Upper%20and%20a%20Heavy%20Lower%20Arm%20Define%20India%E2%80%99s%20K-Shaped%20Trajectory%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F13092208%2FIMG_2134-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20dissonance%20on%20whether%20India%20is%20indeed%20growing%20as%20strongly%20as%20the%20reported%20GDP%20numbers%20is%20a%20matter%20that%20remains%20unsettled%20with%20new%20evidence%20pointing%20towards%20a%20hugely%20distorted%20K-shaped%20trend.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20true%20test%20of%20economic%20growth%20lies%20in%20its%20relevance%20for%20households%20(HH)%2C%20whose%20income%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%20represents%2076%25%20of%20GDP.%20The%20key%20GDP%20growth%20drivers%20in%20recent%20times%20have%20been%20the%20large%20government%20capex%20(7%25%20of%20total%20spending)%20on%20infrastructure%2C%20growing%20over%2060%25%20year-over-year%2C%20and%20the%20strong%20pace%20of%20leveraged%20consumption.%20However%2C%20the%20endogenous%20growth%20components%20exhibit%20structural%20feebleness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFirst%2C%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20data%20(August%202023)%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eproject%20approvals%20by%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%3Cspan%3E%20revealed%20the%20shallowness%20of%20the%20claimed%20private%20capex%20revival.%20While%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20projects%20sanctioned%20by%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%20increased%20by%2014.9%25%20on%20three%20year%20compound%20annual%20growth%20rate%20(CAGR)%20till%20FY23%20at%20Rs%202.7%20trillion%2C%20it%20is%20majorly%20concentrated%20in%20the%20non-industrial%20sector%2C%20i.e.%20the%20infrastructure%20sector%20(Rs%201.6%20trillion)%2C%20mainly%20roads%2C%20dependent%20on%20government%20capex.%20Total%20project%20cost%20excluding%20Infra%20and%20metals%20at%20Rs%20632%20billion%20saw%20a%20contraction%20of%201.6%25%20on%20three-year%20CAGR.%20The%20implied%20lack%20of%20manufacturing%20sector%20jobs%20is%20now%20corroborated%20in%20the%20latest%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20survey%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India%20(October%2C%202023).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESecond%2C%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%2019%25%20year-over-year%20decline%20in%20net%20financial%20savings%20of%20households%20in%20FY19%20(RBI)%20was%20glossed%20over%20as%20an%20indication%20of%20rising%20household%20confidence%20with%20respect%20to%20their%20current%20and%20future%20incomes%2C%20a%20la%20Tobin%E2%80%99s%20wealth%20effect%20(1967).%20Accordingly%2C%20expectations%20of%20higher%20income%20growth%20should%20reduce%20the%20current%20saving%20rate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20facts%20are%20leaning%20towards%20Modigliani%E2%80%99s%20life%20cycle%20hypothesis%20(1955).%20A%20deceleration%20or%20decline%20in%20the%20real%20income%20of%20workers%20(who%20save)%20relative%20to%20those%20of%20retirees%20(who%20dis-save)%2C%20would%20reinforce%20the%20decline%20in%20savings%20as%20consumption%20for%20the%20saving%20cohorts%20gets%20adjusted%20slower%20than%20the%20erosion%20in%20real%20incomes%2C%20thereby%20catalysing%20leveraged%20spending.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20empirical%20estimates%20for%20FY08-FY19%3Cspan%3E%20show%20that%20a%201%20percentage%20point%20decline%20in%20real%20income%20would%20imply%20a%20lesser%20(0.6%20percentage%20point)%20decline%20in%20consumption%20thereby%20resulting%20in%20a%20decline%20in%20HH%20savings%20(-0.3%20percentage%20points).%20These%20estimates%20imply%20that%20the%20contraction%20in%20HH%20savings%20and%20the%20decline%20in%20savings%20rate%20since%20FY12%20is%20due%20to%20slowing%20or%20declining%20incomes%20rather%20than%20bountiful%20incomes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUsing%20the%20combination%20of%20actual%20net%20financial%20savings%20of%20RBI%20data%20(-18.8%25%20year-over-year%20in%20FY23)%2C%20an%20estimated%206.2%25%20growth%20in%20physical%20savings%2C%20and%20a%2012.5%25%20decline%20in%20investments%20in%20gold%20and%20silver%20(trade%20data)%2C%20the%20overall%20savings%20for%20HH%20in%20FY23E%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20contracted%20by%203.7%25%20year-over-year%20in%20FY23E.%20Adding%20household%20savings%20to%20private%20final%20consumption%20expenditure%20we%20get%20household%20incomes%2C%20which%20in%20real%20terms%20grew%20at%203.1%25%20in%20FY23%20and%202.8%25%20on%20a%20four-year%20CAGR%20converting%20into%20real%20per-capita%20income%20growth%20of%201.7%25%20per%20capita%20basis%2C%20ie.%20lowest%20in%2040%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20net-worth%20effect%20from%20the%20rise%20in%20stock%20market%20capitalisation%20has%20little%20impact%20on%20HH%20spending.%20And%20while%20government%20capex%20has%20a%20marginal%20positive%20impact%20on%20HH%20spending%2C%20it%20depresses%20HH%20savings%20significantly.%20The%20impact%20of%20higher%20real%20interest%20rates%20along%20with%20higher%20tax%20incidence%20from%20higher%20government%20capex%20is%20seen%20having%20a%20crowding%20out%20effect%2C%20rather%20than%20crowding%20in%20effect%2C%20as%20is%20commonly%20believed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThird%2C%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20latest%20annual%20periodic%20labor%20force%20survey%20(PLFS)%202022-23%20reported%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20estimated%20unemployment%20rate%20falling%20to%20a%205-year%20low%20at%203.4%25%2C%20-1%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year.%C2%A0%20There%20is%20also%20a%20concomitant%20rise%20in%20the%20rate%20of%20people%20participating%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20(42.4%25%2C%20%2B1.1%20percentage%20points%20YoY%2C%20all%20age%20groups)%20and%20worker-population%20ratio%20(41.1%25%2C%20%2B1.5%20percentage%20points).%20However%2C%20the%20composition%20of%20these%20variables%20reflects%20the%20employment%20problem.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-economic-growth-covid-19-rbi-shaktikanta-das%5C%22%3EFrom%20V-Shaped%20to%20K-Shaped%2C%20Understanding%20the%20Alphabet%20Soup%20of%20Projected%20Indian%20Growth%20Recovery%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rise%20in%20worker%20population%20ratio%20(1.5%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year)%2C%20representing%20the%20employment%20rate%2C%20is%20significantly%20led%20by%20rural%20(%2B1.5%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year)%2C%20mainly%20the%20rural%20young%20cohorts%20with%20(%2B4.3%20percentage%20points)%20and%20a%20contrasting%20trend%20of%20a%20decline%20in%20mature%20rural%20males%20(30%2B%20years).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20sharp%20decline%20in%20rural%20males%20working%20in%20agriculture%20and%20services%2C%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20rural%20construction.%20Females%20have%20moved%20into%20agriculture%20both%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas.%20Work%20in%20the%20overall%20better-paying%20urban%20areas%20has%20contracted%2C%20while%20it%20has%20expanded%20in%20lesser-paying%20agriculture%20and%20rural%20construction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20been%201.5%20percentage%20points%20increased%20proportion%20of%20self-employment%20(57.3%25)%20which%20is%20the%20residual%20impact%20of%20contractions%20in%20regular%20and%20casual%20work%20particularly%20in%20the%20manufacturing%2C%20urban%20construction%2C%20and%20services%20sectors%20along%20with%20a%20substantial%20decline%20in%20casual%20work%20in%20agriculture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccounting%20for%20the%20rise%20in%20%E2%80%98helper%20in%20household%20enterprise%E2%80%99%2C%20represented%20by%20forced%20self-employment%20in%20rural%20areas%20(largely%20unpaid%20labour)%2C%20the%20estimated%20effective%20unemployment%20rate%20has%20risen%20by%200.32%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year%20to%2025.4%25%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proportion%20of%20workers%20engaged%20in%20agriculture%20rose%20again%20to%2045.8%25%20in%20FY23%20(%2B0.3%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year)%20versus%2044%25%20in%20FY18.%20The%20share%20for%20industry%2C%20including%20manufacturing%2C%20declined%200.2%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year%20to%2012.3%25%20and%20so%20did%20the%20share%20for%20services%20(-0.7%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year%20to%2027.8%25).%20Net%20of%20the%20rise%20in%20rural%20and%20decline%20in%20urban%20construction%2C%20the%20share%20of%20workers%20in%20construction%20increased%20to%2013%25%20%2B0.6%20percentage%20points%20year-over-year).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAggregating%20the%20incomes%20from%20regular%20(Rs%2020%2C039%20per%20month%2C%2021%25%20of%20workers)%2C%20casual%20(Rs%208%2C547%2C%2022%25)%2C%20and%20self-employment%20work%20(Rs%2013%2C347%2C%2057%25)%20average%20per%20worker%20income%20based%20on%20PLFS%20is%20estimated%20at%20Rs%2013%2C467%20per%20month%20in%20FY23%20or%205.9%25%20four-year%20CAGR%2C%20translating%20into%200%25%20growth%20in%20real%20terms%20(net%20of%20inflation).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20estimated%201QFY24%20real%20earnings%20growth%20remained%20low%20at%202.9%25%20year-over-year%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20real%20private%20final%20consumption%20expenditure%20growth%20of%206%25%20in%201QFY24%20as%20per%20GDP%20data.%20Thus%2C%20there%20is%20a%20flagrant%20disconnect%20between%20the%20household%20situation%20as%20per%20the%20PLFS%20and%20the%20strong%20real%20GDP%20growth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExhibit%201%3A%20Overall%20worker%20earnings%3A%20Regular%2C%20casual%20and%20self-employed%20(4-year%20CAGR%2C%20%25)%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17115645%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-11.56.29%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17115645%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-11.